  {
    "title": "Breathtaking",
    "rating": 5,
    "travelDate": "2025-09",
    "publishedDate": "2025-09-21",
    "text": "Moremi is a truly spectacular reserve. But not only Moremi — the Khwai Concession area is equally amazing. The amount of wildlife is incredible. We were lucky enough to see a large herd of buffalo, half a dozen lionesses with cubs feeding on a buffalo, two cheetahs (first resting and then active), hippos, hundreds of elephants, zebras, giraffes… simply breathtaking.\n\nYou can visit the reserve on your own, but it’s tricky to navigate, and if you’re inexperienced, it’s hard to know where to look. We did a guided game drive with Godfrey Tlhase from Bush Kings Safaris (bushkingssafaris@gmail.com). He knew the reserve inside out and made sure we had an amazing day. Beyond luck, it was thanks to him that we got to see everything we did.",
