  {
    "title": "Very many animal sightings",
    "rating": 5,
    "travelDate": "2024-10",
    "publishedDate": "2024-12-10",
    "text": "During our round trip through Namibia and Botswana we also spent a few days in the village of Khwai. From there, we drove through the Khwai Community Concession on two days as a self-drive. This is located between the Moremi Game Reserve and Chobe National Park. It is managed by the local community, so you don't have to pay admission. The trails were easily navigable with our Hilux with 4-wheel drive, even if it was partly deep sandy. Part of the route runs along the Okavango, which we definitely liked best. We saw a lot of animals like elephants, giraffes, buffaloes, hippos, zebras, monkeys, eagles, crocodiles,...\nOn the two days we saw very few other vehicles, so you had this natural paradise almost to yourself.",
    "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g316101-d14893679-r983890490-Khwai_Concession-Moremi_Game_Reserve_Okavango_Delta_North_West_District.html",
